In a mixing bowl, cream butter and brown sugar. Beat in egg and vanilla. Combine flour, cinnamon and cloves; gradually add to the creamed mixture. Stir in remaining ingredients. Drop by heaping tablespoonfuls 2 in. apart onto ungreased baking sheets. Bake at 375 degrees F for 12-14 minutes or until golden brown. Remove to wire racks to cool. Store in the refrigerator.